THE FLOATPLANE PILOT WAS ON A POSITIONING FLIGHT TO MEET FISHERMEN AND 
TRANSPORT THEM TO A DIFFERENT LOCATION.  AFTER LANDING ON A RIVER, THE 
PILOT WAS STEP TAXIING INTO A SIDE CHANNEL THAT WAS USED TO LOAD AND 
OFFLOAD PASSENGERS.  HE STATED THAT AS THE FLOATPLANE WAS COMING OFF-
THE-STEP (SLOWING), IT HIT A SUBMERGED SANDBAR THAT COULD NOT BE SEEN 
AND NOSED OVER. 
THE PILOT'S SELECTION OF UNSUITABLE TERRAIN.  FACTORS RELATED TO THE 
ACCIDENT WERE: THE SUBMERGED SAND BAR AND THE PILOT'S EXCESSIVE 
TAXISPEED. 
